Ensure this page is printed and accessible to guide assessment processes
<w:trPr><w:gridAfter w:val="1"/><w:wAfter w:w="3" w:type="pct"/><w:trHeight w:val="324"/></w:trPr><w:tc><w:tcPr><w:tcW w:w="4997" w:type="pct"/></w:tcPr><w:p w14:paraId="7B4AFCAB" w14:textId="55474CC3" w:rsidR="00002A38" w:rsidRPr="002B7EC8" w:rsidRDefault="0000277E" w:rsidP="00894F1D"><w:pPr><w:spacing w:line="276" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:eastAsia="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="24"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="002B7EC8"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:eastAsia="Arial" w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="24"/></w:rPr><w:t>As the assessor
/teacher
, it is your responsibility to clearly communicate all aspects of the assessment process to students and ensure they are absolutely prepared.
 
Do not instruct a student on how to answer a question or complete a task. 
Use the benchmark responses to guide marking and ensure consistency. Keep benchmarks secure and never show or share with students.
Before the Assessment
:
Inform 
s
tudents of 
k
ey 
d
etails
.
d
ate, time, and location of the assessment
w
hat to bring (e.g. identification, materials, tools)
d
ress requirements (e.g. specific attire, PPE/safety gear)
Confirm readiness:
E
nsure students have received all teaching and learning of the unit content
.
 
E
nsure students have 
had time to 
practi
s
e 
related 
skills before the assessment
.
 
Support 
n
eeds:
D
iscuss any reasonable adjustments with students in advance
.
Encourage disclosure of additional learner support needs early so appropriate a
djustments
 can be arranged.
During the Assessment
:
 
Oversee the evidence gathering process to ensure it remains 
valid, sufficient, authentic, current and flexible
.
You may ask students questions to ensure all assessment requirements are addressed.
Ensure the student completes activities at a pace consistent with commercial speed, timing, and productivity expectations.
After the Assessment
:
 
Feedback:
Provide students with timely, meaningful feedback by promptly marking tasks and returning within 2 weeks of the submission date, giving clear written comments, and offering verbal feedback where appropriate.
Refer to the assessment criteria to highlight strengths and areas for improvement
.
Document feedback on EC or hardcopy version of the assessment
.
Recording 
r
esults:
Each assessment component must be marked Satisfactory (S) or Not Yet Satisfactory (NYS).
The unit of competency will be reported as Achieved only when all components are marked Satisfactory.
Evidence 
c
ollection:
Upload all evidence to EC, including any Not Yet Satisfactory attempts
.

Part A: Quiz 
There are 
twenty-two
 (
22
) questions.
Quiz Assessment Instructions 
It is recommended quizzes be completed on Evidence Central (EC). Hardcopies or a combination of both are available if required.
EC quizzes are automatically marked, providing immediate feedback.
Hard copy quizzes must be marked manually.
For hard copy completions, enter results into EC once marking is complete. Upload a PDF copy of the marked quiz to EC.

:
This section allows students to demonstrate required skills and knowledge through work-related 
tasks that 
reflect real or simulated workplace conditions
.
 
The Product Based documents often align or link to the p
ractical 
activities
 observed and recorded in Section 3.
Before the Assessme
nt
:
Refer to your printed copy general instructions Conducting and Managing Assessments.
Review and organise all required materials, tools, and instructions for the task. 
Review the documentation and checklists to understand the required skills, knowledge, and performance standards students must meet for a satisfactory result.
Familiarise students with the activity and review workplace documentation. 
Prior to commencing confirm 
the 
student understand
s
 
the requirements and industry 
expectations of activity.
During
 the Assessment
:
Refer to general instructions Conducting and Managing Assessments
.
Note any deviations from standard procedures and provide justifications for these deviations to maintain transparency in the assessment process.
After the Assessment 
Refer to general instructions Conducting and Managing Assessments
.

Olivia has been operating the angle grinder in Area A for the last hour and has become careless. At 10am, while cutting some rectangular hollow sections (RHS), her hand 
comes in contact with
 the unguarded blade, resulting in a severe cut to the top of her right thumb.
Â 
Olivia is conscious but is pale and bleeding heavily.Â  She sits down and leans against a wall.
 Dean gives Olivia a sterile pad from the first aid kit to put over the thumb for her to apply pressure to stop the bleeding

Â D
ean then reports to the Principal Contractor (Bob Hughes), who provides him the below Incident and Injury Report to compile.

<w:trPr><w:trHeight w:val="1304"/></w:trPr><w:tc><w:tcPr><w:tcW w:w="10341" w:type="dxa"/><w:tcBorders><w:top w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/><w:left w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/><w:bottom w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="auto"/><w:right w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/></w:tcBorders></w:tcPr><w:p w14:paraId="4012F155" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00FF3256" w:rsidRPr="00B13A11" w:rsidRDefault="00FF3256" w:rsidP="002F19DA"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="TitleBullet"/><w:numPr><w:ilvl w:val="0"/><w:numId w:val="0"/></w:numPr><w:spacing w:after="0" w:line="276" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:ind w:left="21"/><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00B13A11"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/></w:rPr><w:t>Before the assessment:
Refer to your printed copy of general instructions Conducting and Managing Assessments.

s
Before starting, explain the task and expectations to the student, and allow time for questions.
<w:trPr><w:trHeight w:val="1304"/></w:trPr><w:tc><w:tcPr><w:tcW w:w="10341" w:type="dxa"/><w:tcBorders><w:top w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/><w:left w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/><w:bottom w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="auto"/><w:right w:val="single" w:sz="4" w:space="0" w:color="000000"/></w:tcBorders></w:tcPr><w:p w14:paraId="268466A4" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00FF3256" w:rsidRPr="00B13A11" w:rsidRDefault="00FF3256" w:rsidP="002F19DA"><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="TitleBullet"/><w:numPr><w:ilvl w:val="0"/><w:numId w:val="0"/></w:numPr><w:spacing w:after="0" w:line="276" w:lineRule="auto"/><w:ind w:left="21"/><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00B13A11"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:cs="Arial"/><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/></w:rPr><w:t>During the assessment:
Refer to your printed copy general instructions Conducting and Managing Assessments.
Observe the student completing each task.
Use the observation checklist to assess their performance against each criterion.
You may answer general or procedural questions, but do not help with completing tasks. 
Record all observations in the assessment tool, including strengths, areas for improvement, and any deviations from standard practice. Ensure your notes align with the criteria.

The student 
MUST
 demonstrate they can safely follow WHS and workplace procedures when manually handling and transporting materials, including:

Undertaking
 Safe Work Australia recommended WHS lifting techniques
Safely and securely placing, relocating and unloading 2 materials using moving equipment

<w:tcPr><w:tcW w:w="4678" w:type="dxa"/><w:vMerge w:val="restart"/></w:tcPr><w:p w14:paraId="7FB30465" w14:textId="63118C76" w:rsidR="00EC6E5E" w:rsidRPr="00733B5B" w:rsidRDefault="00EC6E5E" w:rsidP="00EC6E5E"><w:pPr><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:asciiTheme="minorBidi" w:hAnsiTheme="minorBidi" w:cstheme="minorBidi"/><w:sz w:val="16"/><w:szCs w:val="16"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidRPr="00733B5B"><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:asciiTheme="minorBidi" w:hAnsiTheme="minorBidi" w:cstheme="minorBidi"/><w:sz w:val="16"/><w:szCs w:val="16"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">While undertaking material lifting, the student 
MUST
 use SafeWork Australia manual handling control measures, which 
MAY
 include: 
Using mechanical aids/moving equipment, which 
MAY
 include:
Hand trolleys
Wheelbarrows
Hand pallet truck
Spreader bars, cradles or similar
Team lifting
Wearing the correct PPE (gloves and steel capped boots)
Correct manual lifting techniques, which 
MAY
 include:
Not twisting
Not working with both hands above shoulder height
Not reaching more than 30cms away from the body
Using a straight back
Using bent knees
